---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Clothing Words — Fashion Terms That Score Big"
  description="Clothing terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. TUXEDO (14pts), KIMONO (12pts), PAJAMAS (18pts), KHAKI (16pts). Fashion vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble clothing words, tuxedo scrabble points, kimono scrabble, pajamas scrabble word, khaki scrabble, fashion terms scrabble, clothing vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Clothing Words — Fashion Terms That Score Big","description":"Clothing terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. TUXEDO (14pts), KIMONO (12pts), PAJAMAS (18pts), KHAKI (16pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-clothing-words"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is TUXEDO worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"TUXEDO scores 14 points (T=1, U=1, X=8, E=1, D=2, O=1). The X tile carries most of the value. It's a 6-letter word valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PAJAMAS a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PAJAMAS scores 18 points (P=3, A=1, J=8, A=1, M=3, A=1, S=1). The J=8 tile provides the bulk of scoring power. It's a 7-letter word that can earn a bingo bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What clothing words use K in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"KHAKI (16pts with K=5, H=4, K=5), ANORAK (10pts), and SILK (8pts) all leverage the K=5 tile effectively in clothing contexts."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Clothing Words — Fashion Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Fashion and clothing vocabulary hides some of Scrabble's best premium-tile words. PAJAMAS uses J=8 for 18 points, KHAKI doubles up on K=5 for 16 points, and TUXEDO leverages X=8 for 14. These are everyday words that most players never think to play — giving you an edge when premium tiles feel stuck on your rack.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PAJAMAS (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KHAKI</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TUXEDO</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KIMONO</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Clothing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">PAJAMAS — 18 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, A=1, J=8, A=1, M=3, A=1, S=1 · 7 letters · Uses J tile · Bingo eligible</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">PAJAMAS delivers 18 base points and, as a 7-letter word, qualifies for the 50-point bingo bonus when played from a full rack. That's a potential 68 points from common tiles plus J. The triple-A makes it easy to form when you have vowel-heavy draws alongside J.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👔 TUXEDO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · T=1, U=1, X=8, E=1, D=2, O=1 · Formal suit</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥋 KIMONO</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · K=5, I=1, M=3, O=1, N=1, O=1 · Japanese robe</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧥 ANORAK</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · A=1, N=1, O=1, R=1, A=1, K=5 · Hooded jacket</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">👘 KAFTAN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · K=5, A=1, F=4, T=1, A=1, N=1 · Long garment</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Double-K Power: KHAKI</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🎯 Letter Breakdown</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200"><span class="text-white font-bold">KHAKI</span> — K=5, H=4, A=1, K=5, I=1 = <span class="text-amber-400 font-bold">16 points</span> from just 5 tiles. Uses both K tiles plus H for exceptional efficiency. At 3.2 points per tile, KHAKI outscores most 6-letter words.</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Everyday Clothing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">JACKET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">19pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VELVET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FLEECE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHAWL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TWEED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SILK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Clothing Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PAJAMAS for J+vowel racks:</span> With three A's needed, PAJAMAS works perfectly when your rack is vowel-heavy with J. The P=3 and M=3 add quiet scoring alongside J=8.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TUXEDO places X mid-word:</span> Unlike words ending in X, TUXEDO places it third. This opens different board positions — look for TU- openings on the board to slot in TUXEDO.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JACKET is a hidden gem:</span> J=8, C=3, K=5 make JACKET worth 19 points from 6 tiles. That's over 3 points per tile — exceptional for a common English word everyone knows.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Clothing words excel with <span class="text-white font-medium">J, K, and X tiles</span>. PAJAMAS (J), KHAKI (K+K), TUXEDO (X), JACKET (J+K), and KAFTAN (K+F) all use the most awkward premium tiles. When you draw J or K, think wardrobe before anything else.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best J Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/foreign-words-valid-in-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Foreign Words Valid in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-cooking/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Cooking</span></a>
        
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-ballet/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Ballet</span></a>

          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-martial-arts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Martial Arts</span></a>
</div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid clothing word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
